(5, 'Sensodyne Rapid Relief Toothpaste 80gm', 'Sensodyne Rapid Relief Toothpaste is used for providing quick and lasting relief from sensitive teeth. It forms a protective barrier over exposed dentine, minimises sharp sensations, and strengthens enamel, offering both rapid comfort and long-term protection.', 177.46, 'Personal Care', 12, 'Sensodyne_Rapid_Relief_1.png', '2025-11-14 03:16:38', 'Oral Care', 'Glaxosmithkline Pharmaceuticals Ltd.', 201.12, 13, '[\"Helps provide rapid relief from tooth sensitivity with a protective barrier.\\r\",\"Helps strengthen enamel and manage cavities with fluoride.\\r\",\"Helps remove plaque and surface stains for a brighter smile.\\r\",\"Helps ensure gentle cleaning action and maintains a smooth texture.\"]', 'All Other Combinations (0 Mg)', 'For Rapid Sensitivity Relief: Strontium Acetate forms a protective layer over sensitive areas, helping reduce discomfort caused by temperature changes. This helps provide fast relief and allows you to enjoy hot, cold, sweet, and sour foods without pain.\r\nHelps Strengthen Enamel: Sodium Fluoride helps enhance enamel strength and supports the remineralisation process, making teeth more resistant to decay. This helps protect against cavities and promotes long-term dental health.\r\nFor Effective Plaque Removal: Silica acts as a mild abrasive to help remove plaque and surface stains. It effectively helps clean teeth while being gentle on enamel, contributing to a brighter smile and improved oral hygiene.\r\nFor Gentle Cleaning Action: Sodium Methyl Cocoyl Taurate creates a rich, foamy texture that assists in the even distribution of the toothpaste. It helps ensure effective cleaning while being less irritating to sensitive gums compared to harsher surfactants.', 'Brush two times a day (3 times max.) and spit out.\r\nDon’t swallow.\r\nFor rapid action, first squeeze a pea-sized amount on a clean fingertip and gently rub on the base of the sensitive teeth for 1 minute. Rub on sensitive teeth a maximum of two times per day.', 'Read the label carefully before use.\r\nStore in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight.\r\nProtect it from moisture.\r\nKeep out of reach of children.\r\nFor dental use only.\r\nDo not freeze.\r\nReplace the cap tightly after every use.\r\nSensitive teeth may be a sign of another problem so speak to your dentist about any concerns.\r\nNot suitable for under 12 years.\r\nIf irritation occurs, stop its usage.\r\nTalk to your dentist or doctor as soon as possible if you experience swelling of the mouth or face. ', 'Good to Know:Daily sensitivity protection;Strong teeth and healthy gums;Rapid relief;Long-lasting protection;Helps beat sensitivity fast;It is a vegetarian product\r\nQuick Tips:Brush teeth twice daily for effective sensitivity relief;Use a soft-bristled toothbrush to avoid further gum irritation;Avoid acidic or sugary foods immediately after brushing;\r\nAllergy Information:The toothpaste does not contain common allergens such as gluten, dairy, perfume and sulphates;However, if you have known sensitivities to any ingredients, consult a healthcare professional before use\r\nConcerns It Can Help With:Tooth sensitivity triggered by hot, cold, sweet or sour foods;Cavities and enamel erosion;Plaque buildup and surface stains;Discomfort\r\nArea of Application:Apply toothpaste to teeth and gums during brushing to manage sensitivity, reduce inflammation, and maintain overall oral hygiene\r\nOther Information:Contains approx. 1000 ppm of available fluoride when packed', '[\"How often should I use this toothpaste?:Use the toothpaste twice daily, in the morning and evening, for effective management of sensitivity and overall oral health.\\r\",\"What should I do if I experience irritation?:If irritation occurs, discontinue use and consult a dentist. Ensure you are not allergic to any of the ingredients.\\r\",\"Is this toothpaste effective for severe tooth sensitivity?:The toothpaste is designed for effective relief from mild to moderate