(7, 'Refresh Tears Eye Drops 10ml', 'Refresh Tears Eye Drops help relieve dryness and irritation in the eyes by providing long-lasting moisture. It contains Sodium Carboxymethyl Cellulose, which acts like natural tears to keep eyes hydrated, and Oxychloro Complex, which helps reduce the risk of contamination. These drops soothe redness, burning, and discomfort caused by wind, sun, screen time, or air conditioning. They are gentle, safe for daily use, and suitable for sensitive eyes.', 109.68, 'Health Conditions', 18, '69324f8d37a67_Refresh_Tears_Eye_Drops_1.jpg', '2025-11-14 03:35:30', 'Eye Care', 'Abbvie Therapeutics India Private Limited', 129.04, 15, '[\"Helps relieve dry eyes.\\r\",\"Provides long-lasting moisture.\\r\",\"Mimics natural tears and lubricates the eyes.\\r\",\"Protects against environmental factors.\\r\",\"Soothes irritation, redness, and discomfort.\\r\",\"Supports temporary relief from burning and a gritty sensation.\"]', 'Oxychloro Complex (0.005 %) + Sodium Carboxymethyl Cellulose (0.5 %)', 'Helps Relieve Dry Eye Symptoms: Refresh Tears Eye Drops act as artificial tears, providing long-lasting moisture and lubrication to alleviate dryness caused by reduced tear production, environmental factors, or prolonged screen exposure.\r\nSoothes Eye Irritation and Discomfort: Helps reduce irritation, burning, and the sensation of grittiness in the eyes caused by dryness, wind, dust, air conditioning, or extended use of contact lenses.\r\nProtects and Stabilises the Tear Film: Forms a protective layer over the eye surface, enhancing tear stability and helping manage excessive moisture evaporation, ensuring sustained hydration.\r\nEases Digital Eye Strain: Beneficial for individuals who experience eye fatigue, strain, or dryness due to prolonged computer or mobile screen usage.\r\nSupports Post-Surgical Eye Care: Can be used as part of post-operative eye care to keep the eyes moisturised and comfortable after laser or cataract surgery, as recommended by a doctor.', 'Use it as advised by the physician.', 'Read the label carefully before use.\r\nKeep out of the reach of children.\r\nStore in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight, moisture and heat. \r\nFor external use only.\r\nAvoid touching the nozzle tip to avoid contamination. \r\nUse within one month of opening. \r\nConsult a doctor if you have sensitivities. \r\nInstil as directed by the physician. ', 'Good to Know:Contains an oxychloro complex that manages microbial contamination while being gentle on the eyes;Acts as an artificial tear without medicinal properties, making it suitable for frequent use;Often prescribed for individuals with chronic dry eye syndrome, post-surgical care, or those exposed to harsh environmental conditions\r\nQuick Tips:Ensure hands are clean to avoid contamination while applying the drops;Do not touch the dropper tip to avoid contamination that could lead to eye infections;Discard the bottle if not used within 30 days after opening;Keep in a cool, dry place, away from direct sunlight and heat;Use as recommended by your doctor or as needed for relief\r\nConcerns It Can Help With:Dry Eye Syndrome;Eye Strain;Environmental Irritants;Post-Surgical Eye Care;Contact Lens Discomfort', '[\"What is the use of Refresh Tears Eye Drops?:Refresh Tears Eye Drops are used to relieve dryness and irritation caused by reduced tear production. They lubricate and soothe the eyes, providing quick comfort from burning or discomfort.\\r\",\"Can I use these eye drops while wearing contact lenses?:Remove contact lenses before applying the drops and wait at least 15 minutes before reinserting them.\\r\",\"Can Refresh Tears be used for eye infections?:No, these drops are lubricants and do not manage infections. If you suspect an infection, consult a doctor for a proper regimen.\\r\",\"Can children use these eye drops?:Consult a paediatric ophthalmologist before using on children, though they are generally considered safe for all ages.\"]', 'Dr. Boban Raju ', 'Medical Content Reviewer | 5 years MBBS', 'Dr. Mandeep Chadha', 'Lead Medical Content Reviewer | 11 years MBBS, DNB (OBGY)', 'PRESTIGE OBELISK LEVEL 6 AND LEVEL 7 KASTURBA ROAD , BANGALORE, Karnataka, India - 560001\n\nCountry of origin: INDIA\nExpiry on or after: Augest 2026\n\nIn case of any issues, contact us:\nsupport@medicare.com|06257814252\nAddress: 6th floor, Urmi Corporate Park Street, Atal Sharani Road, Kolkata 700054.', 'We, at Medicare make a diligent attempt to deliver accurate, expert- drafted and thoroughly reviewed medicine related information to our consumers. However, it should, by no means, be considered a substitute for prescription from a certified doctor or a trustworthy doctor-patient relationship. In fact we detest any form of self medication without expert advice. The sole purpose of the information on our portal is to educate our consumers, which helps improve the communication between a doctor and a patient. The information by no means is complete in its entirety and should not be used to diagnose or treat any medical condition. No amount of information can replace the experience and expertise of a doctor, therefore his/her advice always holds priority and should be followed appropriately.'),
(8, 'Nicotex 2mg Paan Flavour Sugar Free Nicotine Gums 12', 'Nicotex 2mg Paan Flavour Sugar-Free Nicotine Gum is used for relieving nicotine cravings and managing your commitment to quitting smoking. This gum helps ensure a controlled release of nicotine, helping to reduce the severity of withdrawal symptoms and cravings without the harmful gases associated with smoking. Experience the paan freshness with each chew, making the quitting process more enjoyable and refreshing. The sugar-free formula helps promote oral health, allowing you to break free from smoking habits without compromising your dental care. Nicotex 2mg Chewing Gum provides small and sustained quantities of nicotine, helping you to receive the necessary support to overcome the challenges of quitting smoking.', 96.80, 'Health Conditions', 25, '693254f2c6ca5_Nicotex_Gums_1.jpg', '2025-11-14 03:40:35', 'Smoking Cessation', 'Cipla Health Limited', 123.01, 20, '[\"Helps reduce nicotine cravings.\\r\",\"Helps promote oral health by assisting in a smoke-free life.\\r\",\"It may improve lung health by reducing smoke and tar intake.\\r\",\"Helps enhance respiratory function.\\r\",\"It may manage coughing and shortness of breath.\\r\",\"Sugar-free formulation.\"]', 'Nicotine Polacrilex: It is a nicotine compound bound to a resin, used in nicotine replacement therapies like Nicotex gum. It releases nicotine slowly when chewed, helping to reduce withdrawal symptoms and cravings associated with quitting smoking. This controlled release mechanism allows users to help manage their nicotine intake gradually, assisting in the cessation process without the harmful effects of tobacco.', 'Helps Reduce Cravings: Nicotex gum helps reduce nicotine cravings by providing a controlled release of nicotine, making it easier to resist the urge to smoke.\r\nHelps Manage Withdrawal Symptoms: It helps alleviate common withdrawal symptoms such as irritability, anxiety, and difficulty concentrating, assisting in a smoother transition to a smoke-free life.\r\nPromotes Oral Health: Being sugar-free, Nicotex gum helps maintain oral hygiene, managing cavities and other dental issues often associated with sugary products.\r\nHelps Improve Lung Health: By helping you quit smoking, Nicotex gum assists in reducing the intake of harmful smoke and tar, allowing your lungs to recover and function more efficiently over time.\r\nRespiratory Function: Using Nicotex to quit smoking may lead to better respiratory function, helping reduce symptoms like coughing and shortness of breath, and improving overall breathing capacity.', 'Chew the gum slowly til you get the taste of nicotine.\r\nPlace and rest between your cheeks and gums.\r\nWhen the taste fades, repeat step 1.', 'Read the label carefully before use.\r\nKeep out of the reach of children.\r\nStore at room temperature.\r\nProtect from excessive heat and direct sunlight.', 'Good to Know:Sugar-free gums;Paan flavour;Helps quit smoking;2 mg for less than 20 cigarettes/day\r\nQuick Tips:Avoid eating or drinking 15 minutes before and during chewing to maximise effectiveness;Gradually reduce the number of gums used per day as your cravings decrease\r\nConcerns It Can Help With:Nicotine cravings;Withdrawal symptoms;Smoking cessation support;Anxiety related to quitting smoking', '[\"How does Nicotex gum help in quitting smoking?:Nicotex gum provides controlled nicotine release to help reduce cravings and withdrawal symptoms, making it easier to quit smoking gradually.\\r\",\"Can I use Nicotex gum while pregnant or breastfeeding?:Consult your healthcare provider before using Nicotex gum if you are pregnant or breastfeeding, as nicotine can affect your baby.\\r\",\"How long should I use Nicotex gum?:Typically, Nicotex gum is used for about 12 weeks, but the duration can vary based on individual needs and the recommendation of a healthcare provider.\\r\",\"Can Nicotex gum cause any side effects?:Some users may experience mild side effects like mouth irritation, hiccups, or an upset stomach. If severe side effects occur, stop using the gum and consult a healthcare provider.\\r\",\"Is Nicotex gum safe for everyone?:Nicotex gum is generally safe for most adults. However, it is important to consult a healthcare provider if you have any medical conditions or are taking other medications.\"]', 'Dr. Divya Mandial', 'Medical Content Writer | 9 years PhD in Chemistry', 'Dr. Mandeep Chadha', 'Lead Medical Content Reviewer | 11 years MBBS, DNB (OBGY)', 'FOFB-11, B WING, FOURTH FLOOR, ART GUILD HOUSE PHOENIX MARKETCITY, L.B.S MARG, KURLA (W EST) , MUMBAI, MAHARASHTRA, INDIA - 400070.\r\n\r\nCountry of origin: INDIA\r\nExpiry on or after: April 2026\r\n\r\nIn case of any issues, contact us:\r\nsupport@medicare.com|06257814252\r\nAddress: 6th floor, Urmi Corporate Park Street, Atal Sharani Road, Kolkata 700054.', 'We, at Medicare make a diligent attempt to deliver accurate, expert- drafted and thoroughly reviewed medicine related information to our consumers. However, it should, by no means, be considered a substitute for prescription from a certified doctor or a trustworthy doctor-patient relationship. In fact we detest any form of self medication without expert advice. The sole purpose of the information on our portal is to educate our consumers, which helps improve the communication between a doctor and a patient. The information by no means is complete in its entirety and should not be used to diagnose or treat any medical condition. No amount of information can replace the experience and expertise of a doctor, therefore his/her advice always holds priority and should be followed appropriately.');
