(15, 'Omron Hem 7121j Blood Pressure Monitor 1', 'Omron HEM-7121 J BP Monitor is used for monitoring blood pressure levels. This digital monitoring device is suitable for professional and home use, designed to track blood pressure and pulse rate. It can detect irregular heartbeat rhythms deviating by more than 25% from the average while measuring blood pressure.\r\n\r\nSpecification of Omron Hem 7121j Blood Pressure Monitor 1\r\nType: Digital Blood Pressure Monitor\r\n \r\nSuitability: Suitable for both professional and home use\r\n \r\nFunctionality: Monitors blood pressure and pulse rate\r\n \r\nMeasurement Method: Oscillometric Method\r\n \r\nMeasurement Range: Blood Pressure: 0-299 mmHg, Pulse Rate: 40-180 beats/min\r\n \r\nCuff Size: Fits arm circumferences of 22-32 cm\r\n \r\nPower Source: 4 AA Batteries (included)\r\n \r\nDisplay: Large LCD screen for clear readings\r\n \r\nMemory: Stores up to 30 measurement readings\r\n \r\nPackage Contents: Omron HEM-7120 BP Monitor, Arm Cuff, Instruction Manual, 4 AA Batteries\r\n \r\nAccuracy: Pressure +- 3mmHg, Pulse +- 5% display reading\r\n \r\nInterface: The monitor offers effortless operation with a single-touch interface.\r\n \r\nBody Movement Detection: It includes body movement detection to reduce errors during measurements.\r\n \r\nMemory: The device retains the last reading in memory for easy reference.\r\n \r\nIntelliSense Technology: Utilising IntelliSense technology, it automatically adjusts pressure for accurate readings.\r\n \r\nCompact and Portable: This fully automatic blood pressure monitor is convenient for use anywhere.\r\n \r\nCuff Wrapping: Its cuff wrapping feature guides proper cuff placement, indicated by \"OK,\" ensuring precise and dependable measurements.', 2270.84, 'Healthcare Devices', 7, 'bp_machine_omron_1.jpeg', '2025-11-18 04:28:22', 'Bp Monitors', 'Omron Healthcare India Pvt Ltd', 2315.12, 2, '[\"Helps measure blood pressure levels and pulse rate.\\r\",\"Convenient design for use at home or on the go.\\r\",\"Stores last readings.\\r\",\"Includes hypertension indicators.\\r\",\"Uses Intellisense Technology.\"]', 'All Other Combinations (0 Mg)', 'Monitoring Blood Pressure: The primary function of the Omron HEM-7120 BP Monitor is to monitor blood pressure levels. It helps users and healthcare professionals assess blood pressure trends over time.\r\nTracking Pulse Rate: In addition to blood pressure, the monitor also tracks pulse rate. Pulse rate variations can indicate changes in heart health and overall cardiovascular function. Monitoring pulse rate alongside blood pressure offers a more comprehensive view of cardiovascular well-being.\r\nDetecting Irregular Heartbeats: One of the advanced features of the Omron HEM-7120 BP Monitor is its ability to detect irregular heartbeat rhythms. It can identify heartbeats that deviate by more than 25% from the average rhythm. \r\nEnsuring Measurement Accuracy: The monitor incorporates IntelliSense technology which automatically adjusts the amount of pressure applied during measurement. This ensures that the cuff inflates to the optimal level for accurate readings. Additionally, it includes body movement detection to minimise errors caused by movement during measurement, further enhancing accuracy.\r\nPortable Healthcare: With its compact design and portability, the Omron HEM-7120 BP Monitor enables users to monitor their blood pressure and pulse rate anywhere, whether at home, at work or while travelling. This promotes consistent monitoring and proactive management of cardiovascular health.\r\nMemory Storage: The device stores the last reading in its memory, allowing users to track their progress over time. This feature is beneficial for individuals who need to monitor changes in blood pressure and pulse rate regularly, as well as for sharing data with healthcare providers during consultations.\r\nUser-Friendly Operation: The monitor is designed for ease of use, featuring one-touch operation for quick and convenient measurements. Additionally, its cuff wrapping guidance system ensures that the cuff is wrapped correctly, indicated by an \"OK\" symbol, leading to more accurate and reliable measurements.', 'Insert the plug into the jack securely.\r\nPut the arm through the cuff loop.\r\nClose the fabric fastener firmly.\r\nWait till the results are displayed.', 'Read the label carefully before use.\r\nStore in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight.\r\nKeep out of reach of children.\r\nRemove the batteries if not in use for three months or longer.', 'Good to Know:Hypertension Indicator: It includes a hypertension indicator that provides an instant visual cue if blood pressure readings fall outside the normal range, helping users identify potential health risks;Comfortable Cuff: The cuff is designed for comfort during use, with a size range that fits most adult arm circumferences (22-32 cm)\r\nQuick Tips:Sit in a relaxed position with your back supported and feet flat on the floor. Place the cuff on your bare upper arm at heart level;Refrain from consuming caffeine or engaging in vigorous exercise at least 30 minutes before taking measurements, as these activities can temporarily affect blood pressure\r\nAllergy Information:In case you experience any side effects, discontinue use and consult your physician\r\nConcerns It Can Help With:Blood pressure levels;Pulse rate', '[\"How do I know if the cuff is wrapped correctly?:The monitor has a cuff wrapping guide that indicates \\\"OK\\\" when the cuff is wrapped correctly, ensuring accurate measurements.\\r\",\"Can multiple users store their readings on the monitor?:The monitor does not have multi-user memory. It stores the last reading taken.\\r\",\"How long does the battery last?:The monitor operates on 4 AA batteries and typically lasts for several months with regular use.\"]', ' Dr. Divya Mandial', 'Medical Content Writer | 9 years PhD in Chemistry', ' Dr. Mandeep Chadha', 'Lead Medical Content Reviewer | 11 years MBBS, DNB 