(16, 'Omron Ne C106 Compressor Nebulizer 1', 'Omron Compressor Nebulizer is used for managing respiratory health at home. Equipped with complete accessories, NE-C106 comes with a mouthpiece, child and adult masks. Specially designed for first-time users, NE-C106 is easy to use and easy to clean.', 1592.00, 'Healthcare Devices', 21, 'Omron_Ne_C106_Compressor_1.jpeg', '2025-11-19 04:09:02', 'Nebulizers Vaporizers', 'Omron Healthcare India Pvt Ltd', 1990.00, 20, '[\"Manages the respiratory health of adults and kids in a family.\\r\",\"Works at an efficient nebulisation rate of 0.3 ml\\/minute.\\r\",\"Provides relief from breathing problems and other respiratory issues.\\r\",\"Ensures efficient absorption and quick delivery of medicines.\"]', 'Specification of Omron Ne C106 Compressor Nebulizer 1\r\nProduct Name: Omron Compressor Nebulizer\r\nProduct Dimensions: 18 x 18 x 21 cm\r\nEffective Medication Delivery: It produces fine aerosol particles for efficient absorption of medicines. It uses a small particle size of MMAD 4.56 µm to reach the lower airway for effective nebulisation.\r\nNebulisation Rate: It works at an efficient nebulisation rate of 0.3 ml/Minute\r\nCompact and Portable: Easy to carry and use at home or on the go. It is simple to clean and disinfect\r\nUser-friendly: It is suitable for both adults and children.\r\nLow noise: It minimises noise for a comfortable experience.\r\nMask and Mouthpiece: It provides options for different user preferences\r\nContents in the box: Nebuliser, inhalation top, medication tank, adult mask, child mask, mouthpiece and vaporiser head\r\nWeight: 1.25 kg\r\nDimensions: 18.0 × 17.0 × 14.0 cm\r\nMedication Cup Capacity: 10 ml\r\nAerosol Output Rate: 0.109 ml/Minute\r\nWarranty: 2 years exchange warranty but not on defective items', 'Asthma Management: The nebuliser is designed to administer asthma medication in aerosol form. It helps in relieving asthma symptoms such as wheezing, coughing and shortness of breath.\r\nCOPD Management: For individuals with Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD), the nebuliser offers a convenient way to deliver bronchodilators and other medications directly to the lungs. This helps in improving lung function and alleviates COPD symptoms like coughing and difficulty breathing.\r\nRespiratory Infection Relief: During respiratory infections such as bronchitis or pneumonia, the nebuliser can be used to deliver antibiotics or other medications directly into the respiratory tract. This targeted delivery helps in combating infections and promoting faster recovery.\r\nAllergy and Sinus Relief: Individuals suffering from allergies or sinus problems can benefit from using the nebuliser to administer saline solutions or prescribed medications. This helps in clearing nasal passages, reducing congestion and relieving allergy symptoms.\r\nPediatric Respiratory Care: The nebuliser is suitable for children with respiratory issues. It provides a gentle and effective way to deliver pediatric medications, ensuring proper treatment and management of respiratory conditions in children.', 'Remove the inhalation top from the medication tank by rotating it anti-clockwise and lifting it.\r\nEnsure the vaporiser head is placed in the medication tank and add the correct amount of prescribed medication.\r\nPut the inhalation top back and attach the mouthpiece or mask to the nebulizer kit tightly.\r\nAttach the air tube, twist it and push it firmly into the air tube connector.\r\nInhale through the mask.', 'Read the label carefully before use.\r\nStore in a cool and dry place away from direct sunlight.\r\nUse as per directions by a healthcare professional.\r\nKeep out of reach of children.', 'Good to Know:User-Friendly Design: The device is easy to operate, making it suitable for individuals of all ages, including the elderly and children. Its intuitive design ensures that anyone can use it with minimal training or instruction;Portable and Compact: With dimensions of 18 x 18 x 21 cm, the nebuliser is compact and portable, making it easy to store and transport. This allows users to carry it while travelling, ensuring they can manage their respiratory health wherever they go;Easy Maintenance: The nebuliser is designed for easy cleaning and maintenance, ensuring long-term reliability and hygiene. Regular cleaning helps minimise the buildup of medication residue and bacteria, ensuring safe use over time;Provides complete accessories which include adult mask, child mask and mouthpiece;Easy to clean and disinfect;Efficient nebulisation rate\r\nQuick Tips:Read the Manual: Before using the nebuliser, thoroughly read the user manual to understand the device\'s operation and safety instructions;Assemble Correctly: Ensure all parts are correctly assembled before each use, including the medication tank, mouthpiece and mask;Proper Cleaning: Clean the nebuliser parts after each use to prevent residue buildup and ensure hygienic operation. Follow the cleaning instructions in the manual;Dry Thoroughly: After cleaning, make sure all parts are completely dry before reassembling to avoid bacterial growth and maintain device efficiency;Avoid any physical damage;Ensure proper hygiene while using the nebuliser;Keep it close to your mouth and nose', '[\"How do I clean the nebuliser?:After each use, disassemble the parts and wash them with warm soapy water. Rinse thoroughly and let them air dry. Refer to the user manual for detailed cleaning instructions.\\r\",\"How do I know if the nebuliser is working properly?:You should see a fine mist coming from the mouthpiece or mask when the nebulizer is in operation. If you do not see a mist or the device is making unusual noises, check for proper assembly and cleanliness or consult the user manual.\\r\",\"What should I do if the nebuliser stops working?:Ensure the device is properly assembled, check the power source and clean the components. If the problem persists, contact customer support or refer to the troubleshooting section in the user manual.\"]', 'Dr. Divya Mandial', 'Medical Content Writer | 9 years PhD in Chemistry', 'Dr. Mandeep Chadha', ' Lead Medical Content Reviewer | 11 years MBBS, DNB (OBGY)', '6th Floor, B-Block, Sewa Tower, Plot no.19, Sector -18, Udyog Vihar, Maruti Industrial Complex, Gurugram, Haryana 122008\r\n\r\nCountry of origin: VIETNAM\r\nExpiry on or after: March 2026\r\n\r\nIn case of any issues, contact us:\r\nsupport@medicare.com|06257814252\r\nAddress: 6th floor, Urmi Corporate Park Street, Atal Sharani Road, Kolkata 700054.', 'We, at Medicare make a diligent attempt to deliver accurate, expert- drafted and thoroughly reviewed medicine related information to our consumers. However, it should, by no means, be considered a substitute for prescription from a certified doctor or a trustworthy doctor-patient relationship. In fact we detest any form of self medication without expert advice. The sole purpose of the information on our portal is to educate our consumers, which helps improve the communication between a doctor and a patient. The information by no means is complete in its entirety and should not be used to diagnose or treat any medical condition. No amount of information can replace the experience and expertise of a doctor, therefore his/her advice always holds priority and should be followed appropriately.'),
